Author: dukeleto#7326
Content: there is a simple way to count how many sprout/sapling joinsplits are in an xtn, if there are none => give that error

Author: dukeleto#7326
Content: ` if (tx.vShieldedSpend.empty() && tx.vShieldedOutput.empty() && tx.vjoinsplit.empty())`

Author: dukeleto#7326
Content: @TonyL untested, but that is what you need

Author: dukeleto#7326
Content: if that is true => throw nice error

Author: dukeleto#7326
Content: first 2 are for sapling, last one is sprout, so the code supports chains with sprout joinsplits
